A '''lighthouse museum''' is a [[museum]] specializing in the display of [[historical]] objects relating to [[lighthouse]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theday.com/article/20170511/NWS01/170519862|title=Stonington borough approves lighthouse museum addition|publisher=[[The Day (New London)|The Day]]|author=Joe Wojtas|date=May 11, 2017|accessdate=February 27, 2018}}</ref> These museums are either stand alone buildings or are present in lighthouses that are active or inactive. Objects displayed include tools lighthouse keepers used at the time in their everyday lives to maintain the light as well as historic objects such as the [[Fresnel lens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lighthousefriends.com/light.asp?ID=546|title=Portland Head Light|work=Lighthousefriends|accessdate=February 27, 2018}}</ref> In addition to navigation, lighthouses in general continue to operate almost as "small [[maritime museum]]s".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visit-massachusetts.com/state/lighthouses/|title=Massachusetts lighthouses tell the story of seafaring life and dangers|work=New England.com|accessdate=March 19, 2018}}</ref>

==Lighthouse museums==
{{refimprove|section|date=March 2018}}
[[File:Naturaliste lighthouse gnangarra 04.JPG|thumb|light units on display in the former [[Lighthouse keeper|keeper]]'s residence]]

