'''Mintage World''' is a virtual online museum of coins, currency notes and postage stamps. It was launched on April 23, 2016, at coin & philately fair held at the [[World Trade Centre, Mumbai|World Trade Center, Mumbai]].<ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/mumbai/devendra-fadnavis-launches-online-numismatic-museum-2767505/ Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis launches online numismatic museum] The Indian Express, April 24, 2016</ref> <ref>[http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/those-who-do-not-know-indias-history-have-no-future-devendra-fadnavis/articleshow/51955556.cms Those who do not know India's history have no future: Devendra Fadnavis] The Economic Times, April 24, 2016</ref>

It is an online platform for learning about ancient coins, notes and stamps and the history of [[Numismatics]], [[Notaphily]] and [[Philately]].<ref>[http://www.asianage.com/mumbai/coins-part-cultural-heritage-cm-devendra-fadnavis-747 Coins part of cultural heritage: CM Devendra Fadnavis] The Asian Age, April 24, 2016</ref> The virtual online museum has information on more than sixty thousand coins, fifteen hundred notes and five thousand stamps from ancient to modern times across the world. It classifies exhibits according to ancient, medieval, colonial and modern.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/news/cm-unveils-online-vintage-coin-museum/article8515606.ece CM unveils online vintage coin museum] The Hindu, April 24, 2016</ref>

The museum was started by Mr. Sushil Kumar Agarwal, MD and CEO of [[Ultra Media & Entertainment|Ultra Media & Entertainment Pvt. Ltd.]]<ref>[http://www.indianshowbiz.com/?p=117103 World’s 1st online museum for Vintage & Current Coins, Stamps & Currency Notes] Indian Show Biz, April 24, 2016</ref>

