{{Infobox journal | title = Praksis | cover = | editor = | discipline = [[Marxism]] | language = Turkish | abbreviation = Praksis | publisher = Dipnot Yayınları | country = Turkey | frequency = Triannually | history = 2001–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.praksis.org | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 57713340 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1302-8618 | eISSN = }} '''''Praksis''''' is a [[Marxist]] interdisciplinary [[academic journal]] related to social sciences that has been published in Turkey since 2001. The name of the journal is taken from the Turkish spelling of the word "[[Praxis School|praxis]]". The journal supports [[historical materialism]] in theory. Among the most discussed topics are class struggle, contemporary Marxist currents, intellectuals, Turkish politics, and international developments. There is also a socialist band called "Praksis" from Turkey/Izmir.
