A '''sulphobe''' is a film composed of [[formaldehyde]] and [[thiocyanates]] alleged to have lifelike properties. Sulphobes were a subject in the researches of [[Alfonso L. Herrera]], a biologist who studied the [[origin of life]].<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.96.2479.14 | title = A New Theory of the Origin and Nature of Life | year = 1942 | last1 = Herrera | first1 = A. L. | journal = Science | volume = 96 | pages = 14 | pmid = 17838641 | issue = 2479| bibcode = 1942Sci....96...14H }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | doi =10.1007/BF00700417 | title =Alfonso L. Herrera: A Mexican pioneer in the study of chemical evolution | year =1995 | last1 =Negrón-Mendoza | first1 =A. | journal =Journal of Biological Physics | volume =20 | pages =11}}</ref>

